<FILEID>AP-NR-03-25-88 0750EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-Martin     03-25 0168</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Martin,0172</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dino Gets Out of Hospital, But Must Leave `Rat Pack' Tour</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Singer Dean Martin was released from the
hospital Thursday, but his doctor ordered him to stay off the rest
of the spring leg of the ``Rat Pack'' reunion tour with pals Frank
Sinatra and Sammy Davis Jr.
   Cedars-Sinai spokesman Ron Wise said Martin left the hospital
around 10 a.m. Thursday to continue his recuperation at home.
   The entertainer was hospitalized Monday for treatment of what
Cedars-Sinai Medical Center officials said was an old kidney
ailment that flared up shortly after he, Sinatra and Davis had
embarked on a reunion concert tour.
   Wise said Martin's physician, Dr. Charles Kivowitz, wants the
entertainer to remain at home for three to four weeks before going
back to work, however.
   The tour of the so-called ``Rat Pack'' buddies, who appeared in
Las Vegas and films together during their careers, will continue
this month and next without Martin, but resumes July 7 in Los
Angeles.
</TEXT>
