<TEXT>
   A group of South Florida
homosexuals hopes to attend the Democratic National Convention in
Atlanta this summer to push for expanded gay rights and increased
funding for AIDS patients.
   Key West lawyer Fred Butner is on a slate of 10 gay Democrats
running as delegates and alternates in Monroe, Dade, Broward and
Palm Beach counties.
   Lynda Russell, the state Democratic Party's deputy director,
