<TEXT>
   Two education groups that say children are
being subjected to tests too early in life are calling on schools
not to subject kindergarten children to standardized exams that
determine advancement to first grade.
   ``Our children are being tested too early and failed too soon,
and parents should ask for what purpose,'' said Sue Bredekamp,
