<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Gulf-Pool     03-25 0350</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Gulf-Pool,0359</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Abandoned Iranian Boat Found by U.S. Navy</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Gulf Rdp</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RICHARD PYLE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ABOARD USS REUBEN JAMES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This U.S. Navy frigate found and
retrieved an armed power launch apparently abandoned by the
Iranians in the Strait of Hormuz.
   The craft, with a twin-barrel 25mm anti-aircraft gun mounted on
its bow and protected by a canvas, was brought alongside the USS
Reuben James in a tense, three-hour operation hampered by high seas
Thursday.
   The find could advance American knowledge of how the Iranians
operate in the Persian Gulf, Navy officials said. ``I'm not sure
what all this is going to lead to in the way of intelligence,''
said Cmdr. John J. Kieley III, skipper of the Reuben James. ``But I
think it will go a long way in helping us to understand the kind of
thing that goes on out here.''
   The captain repeatedly tried to approach the boat late Thursday
with his 443-foot frigate when it was found about 12 miles off the
coast of Oman at the entrance to the Strait of Hormuz. But seas up
to 10 feet and strong winds made maneuvering difficult, and the
Irananian boat disappeared into the darkness until it was relocated
two hours later.
   Two seamen was finally lowered onto the deck of the Iranian boat
from a helicopter hovering overhead.
   ``I was scared,'' said eight-year Navy veteran Tony Santos, 24,
of Bozeman, Mont., one of the lowered seamen. ``I didn't know what
to expect, whether it was booby trapped or whether to look for
someone lying down on the boat or what.''
   Lines were attached, and the Iranian craft was tied to the
frigate's stern for towing.
   Its rusty but functioning anti-aircraft gun had ammunition boxes
attached and was ready for firing. Spent shells littered the floor
of the boat, along with several sealed boxes of ammunition, cans of
diesel fuel and other items.
   The area where the ship was found is close to main shipping
lanes where tankers and other commercial vessels are frequently
attacked by Iran's naval frigates and armed patrol boats.
</TEXT>
