<HEAD>Train Hits Nursery School Bus, 15 People Dead</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with death toll revised to 15,
sted 16, and other details. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>JUNEDA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger train today struck a bus
carrying nursery school pupils home for the Easter holidays,
killing 15 people, including 10 children, a government spokesman
said.
   The victims included six boys and four girls, said Francisco
Castillo, a spokesman for Lerida province. The bus driver and four
teachers also were killed, he said.
   Eighteen children were injured, four of them seriously. The
children, who attended the Los Angeles nursery school in Juneda,
were between the ages of 1 and 6.
   The accident occurred at a rail crossing between the towns of
Juneda and Puigvert, 11 miles southeast of the city of Lerida in
northeastern Spain.
   The state-owned railway RENFE said the bus driver apparently
ignored a clearly marked stop sign and moved to go over the rail
crossing at the same time a RENFE passenger train passed by.
   Railway officials said no injuries were reported among
passengers of the train, which was headed for the coastal city of
Tarragona from Lerida.
   It was the second fatal train accident in Spain in a month. On
March 3, eight people died when one RENFE train rammed into a
second standing in a railway yard in a station in the northern city
of Valladolid.
</TEXT>
