<HEAD>Reagan to Nominate O'Neal to Mine Safety Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan intends to nominate David
O'Neal to be assistant secretary of labor for mine safety and
health, the White House announced today.
   If confirmed by the Senate, O'Neal would succeed David A. Zegeer.
   Since 1985, O'Neal has served as deputy director of the Bureau
of Land Management at the Interior Department. Before that he was
president of O'Neal Inns Ltd from 1984-86, president of O'Neal
Printing, 1982-84, and executive vice president of Aviation Systems
International from 1981-82.
   O'Neal, a native of Belleville, Ill., graduated from St. Louis
College of Pharmacy in 1962. He served in the U.S. Marine Corps
from 1956-59.
