<HEAD>Two Escape, Leave Thank You Note</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIDALIA, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two prisoners escaped from the Concordia
Parish jail and left a note thanking deputies for the tools they
used, officials said.
   George Hunter III, 28, and Ronnie Batteaste, 28, escaped late
Wednesday or early Thursday, authorities said.
   Deputies said the men used a hammer, srewdriver and hacksaw to
dismantle a light fixture in their cell block and crawl through a
ventilation shaft.
   ``Thank you for leaving the escape route and a box of tools,''
the note said. ``See you later, suckers.''
   Batteaste was being held on charges of burglary and escape
stemming from earlier incident. Hunter escaped the same jail in
1984 while he was being held on armed robbery charges. He was
caught more than a year later in California.
   Hunter was convicted on the armed robbery charges Wednesday in
District Court and was to have been sentenced Friday. He faced a
possible maximum of 99 years in prison for each of two counts.
