<HEAD>Bandits Rob Hospital Payroll Office</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seven bandits burst into a hospital Friday, disarmed
four guards and took about $565,000 in cash from the payroll
office, police said.
   No injuries were reported in the holdup at the Centro
Traumatologico Hospital.
   Police said they did not exclude the possibility that the
bandits, who were armed with pistols and a submachine gun, were
terrorists seeking cash to finance their activities.
   It was the second holdup at a Rome hospital in two days.
   On Thursday, five gunmen disguised as doctors held up a bank
inside the Santo Spirito hospital and fled with about $685,000 that
had just arrived by armored car to pay employees' salaries.
   Wearing white doctor's jackets, the bandits pistol-whipped a
guard and a radiologist before fleeing on motorscooters, police
said.
