<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rep. James Howard, D-N.J., chairman of the
House Public Works Committee, died today, a day after suffering a
heart attack while playing golf, his office said.
   Howard, 60, a 22-year House veteran, collapsed Thursday on a
suburban Maryland golf course, according to his office. His staff
said he suffered a heart attack and cardiac arest.
   Doctors labored for nearly two hours to start the Spring Lake
Heights, N.J., lawmaker breathing on his own after the attack .
Howard had not regained consciousness since he was stricken.
   Howard, who had suffered two previous heart attacks, was revived
by doctors at Montgomery General Hospital in Olney, Md. He was then
rushed by helicopter to the sophisticated cardiac unit at the
Hospital Center here.
   A former Wall Township schoolteacher and principal, Howard has
been in Congress since 1965. He is the second most senior member of
