<HEAD>29 Leftists Escape Military Prison</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: UPDATES thruout with number of escapees at 29, sted 28; ADDS
that some facing death penalty. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>ISTANBUL, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Twenty-nine leftist inmates tunneled
their way out of a military prison, Istanbul's deputy governor said
Friday.
   Ihsan Yalcin told The Associated Press by telephone that the
inmates escaped from the Metris military prison Thursday night
through a 60-yard long tunnel they had dug earlier.
   The Anatolia news agency said nine of the inmates faced the
death penalty and eight were serving life sentences.
   Yalcin said 19 of the escapees were members of the outlawed
Turkish Workers' and Peasants' Liberation Army and that the rest
belonged to other outlawed leftist organizations.
