<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--MilitaryExercise     03-25 0181</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Military Exercise,180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>US To Stage Exercise In Atlantic, Gulf, Caribbean</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United States will stage its biannual
``Ocean Venture'' exercise during April with more than 40,000
servicemen participating, the Pentagon said Friday.
   The exercise will be staged in the Atlantic Ocean, Gulf of
Mexico and Caribbean Sea as well as at selected bases in Florida
and Puerto Rico, the Pentagon said. It will begin on April 1 and
extend through April 22.
   ``Ocean Venture exercises are held every two years and are
designed to demonstrate the joint forces capability of the U.S.
Atlantic Command to rapidly project military power,'' the Pentagon
said.
   ``Ocean Venture 88 will exercise command-and-control of
participating forces; their rapid deployment and employment, as
well as the integration of military reserve units into the active
force.''
   The exercise will include aircraft carrier operations; airborne,
amphibious and infantry assaults; live-fire exercises, and port
security, harbor defense and combat search and rescue drills, the
Pentagon said.
   It added that ``members of the Dutch Royal Marines from the
Netherlands Antilles will also participate in this exercise.''
</TEXT>
