<HEAD>Lawmakers Call For Congressional Hearing On Navy Caucus Decision</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Washington state lawmakers called Friday for a
Senate hearing on the Navy's decision to bar civilian employees of
the Puget Sound Naval Shipyard from participating in the state's
March 8 presidential caucuses.
   While the employees were allowed to attend the caucuses, the
Navy said that a provision of the Hatch Act forbade them from
speaking. Some of the employees reportedly wore gags when they
attended the caucuses.
