<HEAD>Casey Won't Endorse Before Pennsylvania Primary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARRISBURG, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gov. Robert P. Casey said Friday he will
not endorse any of the Democratic presidential hopefuls prior to
Pennsylvania's April 26 primary.
   At a news conference, Casey gave two reasons for his decision.
   ``It was clear a number of Democratic candidates have
substantial support amng the voters of this state,'' he said,
adding that voters should have a chance to express their views.
   Casey also said his supporters have pledged to a number of the
candidates and if he made a choice it would undercut their
positions.
   The governor said he was not leaning toward any of the five
Democrats still in the field.
