<HEAD>Nineteen Workers Killed In Dormitory Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pre-dawn fire Friday killed 19
female workers in a factory dormitory on the outskirts of Seoul and
badly injured four, police reported.
   Police officials said 17 workers suffocated from poisonous fumes
as the fire consumed rolls of fabric and two workers died in a
hospital of injuries.
   They said 28 women in all were asleep on the third-floor
dormitory of a building in Seoul's Anyang district when fire broke
out about 2 a.m. Rolls of fabric were stored in the stairway
between the second and third floors, police said.
   Five workers escaped unhurt.
   The cause of the fire is under invetigation, police said.
