<1ST_LINE>r f BC-SouthKorea-GNP     03-25 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-South Korea-GNP,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Central Bank Announces Preliminary GNP Figures for 1987</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korea's gross national product
grew 12 percent last year, down from a growth rate of 12.3 percent
in 1986, the Bank of Korea announced Friday.
   The GNP totaled $118.6 billion last year, compared $98.3 billion
in 1986, according to the central bank's preliminary estimate.
   The central bank had projected a growth rate of 12.2 percent for
1987, based on economic growth in the first three quarters of the
year.
   Bank officails said exports, the mainstay in the Korean ecnomy,
accounted for 46.1 percent of the GNP last year when Korean exports
soared to a record $47.2 billion, up 36.2 percent from a year
earlier.
   The sharp rise in dollar value of the GNP, which measures the
nation's output of goods and services, was attributed partly to the
revaluation last year of the Korean won against the U.S. dollar.
The won rose 8.7 percent last year.
</TEXT>
