<TEXT>
   Bruno's Inc., Alabama's largest grocery
chain, has agreed to buy 82 Piggly Wiggly stores in Georgia for $30
million in stock, company officials said.
   Bruno's, a Birmingham-based company, already has 123
supermarkets. Under the agreement, Bruno's will buy Piggly Wiggly
Southern, a Vidalia holding company that owns stores in central and
southern Georgia.
   The purchase, announced Thursday, includes a 585,000-square-foot
warehouse in Vidalia that serves all 82 stores.
   Bruno's operates supermarkets under the names of Bruno's, Food
World, Foodmax and Consumer Warehouse Foods in Alabama, Georgia,
Tennessee and Florida. With the addition of the Piggly Wiggly
stores, it will have more than 200 stores.
   The Georgia stores that Bruno's plans to buy will continue to
operate under the Piggly Wiggly name, said Bruno's spokeswoman Beth
Dunnaway.
