<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Checks treated with a chemical that causes them
to disintegrate into confetti shortly after being deposited have
shown up in at least two states, costing banks nearly $70,000 since
the beginning of the year, police said.
   A check clearinghouse said Thursday it has warned 142 banks to
be on the lookout for the dissolving checks, which may have an
unusual odor and feel oily.
   The checks have turned up at five or six banks in the Chicago
area and at one in Tennessee. Authorities also are looking into a
report of a possible dissolving check in Indiana.
