<1ST_LINE>r f PM-TreasuryAuction     03-25 0103</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Auction,0108</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Yields on Four-Year Notes Lowest in Nine Months</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on four-year Treasury notes have
declined in the government's latest auction to the lowest level in
nine months.
   The average yield in Thursday's auction was 7.90 percent, down
from 8.33 percent at the last auction on Dec. 23.
   It was the lowest rate since four-year notes averaged 7.89
percent last June 24. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate
of 7~ percent, with each $10,000 in face value selling for
$9,991.60.
   A total of $6.5 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$17.2 billion.
</TEXT>
